<collectionCode box="[793,899,1629,1655]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
being here designated the 
<typeStatus box="[1201,1307,1629,1655]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen has the following data label: Type H. 
<collectionCode box="[686,705,1665,1691]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">T</collectionCode>
. [red-rimmed circular label, printed]\ B.M. 
<collectionCode box="[1185,1255,1665,1691]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">TYPE</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[1260,1329,1665,1691]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">HYM</collectionCode>
. [printed] 17b 1171 [handwritten]\ [circular label] Braz [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1874" box="[903,1182,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perforator">
<emphasis box="[903,1109,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Centris perforator</emphasis>
Smith
</taxonomicName>
(Type). [handwritten]. The 
<typeStatus box="[277,380,1737,1763]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">lectotype</typeStatus>
